  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">In the equation above, <span class=\"italic\">T</span> represents Brittany&rsquo;s total take-home pay, in dollars, for her first week of work, where <span class=\"italic\">h</span> represents the number of hours she worked that week and 1,000 represents a sign-on bonus. If Brittany&rsquo;s total take-home pay was $1,576, for how many hours was Brittany paid for her first week of work?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">16</p>\n"
    },
